THE National Bank of Commerce (NBC) has expressed its commitment to stimulate economic growth in the Northern Zone regions by supporting government efforts in promoting the tourism, agriculture, livestock and trade sectors. The bank’s senior officials including board of directors’ representatives and heads of various departments of the bank over the weekend visited Manyara, Arusha and Karatu regions aiming to meet their clients in the mentioned sectors so that together they can discuss business opportunities, growth plans and new services offered by the bank. The NBC’s Head of Retail Banking, Elibariki Masuke said the move enabled them to meet their customers, introduce their new services and products as well as receive feedback on the needs of their customers, especially at the time when the regions are in the process of further improving the tourism industry. “The government has made great strides in boosting the tourism industry and so we as key stakeholders have seen fit to support her in achieving her ambition. Through our NBC Business Club product, we have been able to meet our target audience and we have been able to discuss and present our new products that are in line with our core mission of promoting tourism,” he said. For his part, NBC’s Director for Business Development, Elvis Ndunguru said through the commitment, the bank hopes to further improve its POS payment service to increase efficiency in revenue collection, including foreign exchange.